WorldStage Newsonline– Mr Osinakachukwu Ideozu, the Senator representing Rivers West, has defected from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to the All Progressives Congress (APC). Majority Leader of the Senate, Ahmed Lawan who announced Osinakachukwu’s defection at plenary on Wednesday welcomed and congratulated him for joining the majority party. With this, the three senators from Rivers, a PDP controlled state, are now members of the APC. The others are Sen. Andrew Uchendu (Rivers East) and Magnus Abe (Rivers South East).